item.description:
This will be an "intermediate and up" level meetup. It will be outdoors on a grass field.

Intermediate - Players with firm understanding of game strategy. Should have a good grasp of skills (passing, setting, hitting) and be able to move around to cover areas of the court.

Location: Grass fields at Sidney and Pacific Street in Cambridge.

Access by T: Central Square stop. Walk down Mass Ave towards MIT and make a right on Sidney Street (There's a restaurant called Asgard on the corner of Sidney Street). Walk down Sidney street about 4 blocks to Pacific Street. It's about a 5-10 minute walk from the T stop.

Parking: There are spots on one side of Tudor Street between Sidney and Brookline that are free to park at on weekends. It is the side of the street opposite the side with the parking meters.
item.name: Cambridge Outdoor Volleyball Sat 7/11 @ 1 PM (Intermediate+)
